
WSO2 Web Services Framework for Ruby (WSO2 WSF/Ruby)
====================================================

LATEST VERSION
--------------
Details of the latest version can be found on the WSO2 WSF/Ruby project
page under http://wso2.org/projects/wsf/ruby


INTRODUCTION
------------
WSF/Ruby is the Ruby language extension to WSO2 WSF/C
[http://www.wso2.org/projects/wsf/c]. This version enables you to 
consume/provide Web Services both with REST and with the power of
WS-* stack including WS-Reliable Messaging, WS-Security, WS-Addressing
and MTOM Attachments. WSF/Ruby distinguishes itself being the first and 
the only Web Services Framework in Ruby to support this stack of 
WS specifications. (See below for the complete Features list) 


FEATURES
--------
  - Support for REST
  - Support for SOAP 1.1
  - Support for SOAP 1.2
  - Support for WSDL 1.1
  - Support for WSDL 2.0
  - Support for SOAP MTOM
  - Support for WS-Addressing
  - Support for WS-Security (with Rampart)
  - Support for WS-Policy
  - Support for WS-SecurityPolicy
  - Support for WS-ReliableMessaging (with Sandesha)


INSTALLATION
------------

Please refer README.INSTALL(or README.INSTALL_WIN32, for Windows platform)

LICENCING
---------

WSO2 WSF/Ruby is released under Apache Licence Version 2.0
Please see the file called LICENCE.

CONTACTS
--------

  o If you want freely available support for using WSO2 WSF/Ruby please
    join the WSO2 WSF/Ruby user community by subscribing to users mailing
    list, wsf-ruby-user@wso2.org by sending an email to 
    'wsf-ruby-user-request@wso2.org' with the subject 'subscribe'.

  o If you have a bug report for WSO2 WSF/Ruby please go log a Jira issue
    at https://wso2.org/jira/browse/WSFRUBY

  o If you want to participate in actively developing WSO2 WSF/Ruby please
    subscribe to the 'wsf-c-dev@wso2.org' by sending and email to 
    wsf-c-dev-request@wso2.org with the subject 'subscribe'.


TRAINING
--------

WSO2 Inc. offers a variety of professional Training Programs, including
training on general Web services as well as WSO2 WSF/Ruby.

For additional support information please refer to
http://wso2.com/training/course-catalog/


SUPPORT
-------

WSO2 Inc. offers a variety of development and production support
programs, ranging from Web-based support up through normal business
hours, to premium 24x7 phone support.

For additional support information please refer to http://wso2.com/support/
